Reasoning: The paper deals with decision problems defined over Boolean circuits and Boolean formulae, which are topics related to logic and complexity theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the study of sets of Boolean functions and their properties, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the use of Post's lattice, a well-known tool in the study of Boolean functions, could also make the paper relevant to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
